-1}$. As a result, we find that, for searches conducted at 1.4 GHz, the\noptimal diameter of single-dish radio telescopes to detect FRBs is 30-40 m. The\npossible astrophysical implications of the measured event rate density are also\ndiscussed in the current paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 16:50:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2020 06:12:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-22"}
