twork for relative gravimeters\nand repeatedly measured its connections during the construction of the atom\ninterferometer. We additionally developed a 3D model of the host building to\ninvestigate the self-attraction effect and studied the impact of mass changes\ndue to groundwater hydrology on the gravity field around the reference\ninstrument. The gravitational effect from the building 3D model is in excellent\nagreement with the latest gravimetric measurement campaign which opens the\npossibility to transfer gravity values with an uncertainty below the 10\nnm/s$^2$ level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 17:42:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 29 Nov 2020 12:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-01"}
