- without adding any further\nmass -- the flare provokes no severe changes on the rotation curve. The flare\nmainly provokes a faster velocity decrease in the outer part of the Galaxy\n($r\\gtrsim 14$ kpc). But we also have obtained a slight velocity increase in\nthe first kiloparsecs after the starting point of the flare.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 20:02:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Mar 2020 16:05:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-16"}
