 dynamical instabilities and chaotic evolution\nare not uncommon among planetary systems. They also suggest that the efficiency\nof the planetary formation process in producing high-multiplicity systems is\nlikely to be higher than that suggested by their currently known population.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Mar 2020 15:31:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Mar 2020 11:56:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-22"}
